  "symptom1Title": "Morning Sickness",
  "symptom1ShortDescription": "Nausea and vomiting, usually in early pregnancy.",
  "symptom1FullDescription": "Nausea is very common due to rising hormones (hCG). Usually fades by week 16. \n\nTips: Eat small meals, ginger tea, stay hydrated.",
  "symptom2Title": "Round Ligament Pain",
  "symptom2ShortDescription": "Sharp pain in lower belly or groin.",
  "symptom2FullDescription": "Sharp jabbing pain felt in the lower abdomen or groin area on one or both sides. Caused by the stretching of ligaments supporting the uterus.",
  "symptom3Title": "Bleeding / Spotting",
  "symptom3ShortDescription": "Any vaginal bleeding.",
  "symptom3FullDescription": "Light spotting can happen after sex or an exam, but bright red blood or heavy flow is NOT normal. \n\nAction: Call your doctor immediately.",
  "symptom4Title": "Swelling (Edema)",
  "symptom4ShortDescription": "Swollen feet and ankles.",
  "symptom4FullDescription": "Mild swelling is normal. However, sudden swelling in face or hands combined with headache could be Preeclampsia.",
  "symptom5Title": "Headaches",
  "symptom5ShortDescription": "Mild to severe head pain.",
  "symptom5FullDescription": "Common due to hormones/dehydration. \n\nWarning: Severe headache that won't go away could be a sign of high blood pressure.",
  "symptom6Title": "Braxton Hicks",
  "symptom6ShortDescription": "Practice contractions.",
  "symptom6FullDescription": "Irregular, non-painful tightening of the belly. They go away if you move or drink water. \n\nIf they become regular/painful -> Call doctor.",
  "symptom7Title": "Fatigue",
  "symptom7ShortDescription": "Extreme tiredness.",
  "symptom7FullDescription": "Very common due to hormonal changes and increased energy demands. Rest when possible.",
  "symptom8Title": "Breast Tenderness",
  "symptom8ShortDescription": "Sore or sensitive breasts.",
  "symptom8FullDescription": "Caused by rising hormones. Usually improves after the first trimester.",
  "symptom9Title": "Frequent Urination",
  "symptom9ShortDescription": "Needing to pee more often.",
  "symptom9FullDescription": "Pressure on the bladder and hormonal changes cause frequent urination. Normal unless painful.",
  "symptom10Title": "Constipation",
  "symptom10ShortDescription": "Difficulty passing stools.",
  "symptom10FullDescription": "Hormones slow digestion. Increase fiber, fluids, and gentle movement.",
  "symptom11Title": "Heartburn",
  "symptom11ShortDescription": "Burning sensation in chest or throat.",
  "symptom11FullDescription": "Caused by relaxed digestive muscles and pressure from the uterus.",
  "symptom12Title": "Shortness of Breath",
  "symptom12ShortDescription": "Feeling out of breath.",
  "symptom12FullDescription": "Mild breathlessness is normal. Sudden or severe shortness of breath needs medical attention.",
  "symptom13Title": "Lower Back Pain",
  "symptom13ShortDescription": "Aching lower back.",
  "symptom13FullDescription": "Caused by posture changes and extra weight. Gentle stretching may help.",
  "symptom14Title": "Leg Cramps",
  "symptom14ShortDescription": "Painful cramps, usually at night.",
